The paper deals with the problem of robots assisting the disabled or elderly, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep neural networks and machine learning techniques for learning from demonstration suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of vision components and inverse kinematics suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
